This constants.js provides:
Organized Configuration:
Extension Metadata: Version, author, repository links
Environment Settings: Development/staging/production flags with debug options
Storage Keys: Centralized key names for all storage operations
Message Types: Standardized communication protocol between contexts
Engine Configs: OCR, translation, and CV engine settings
UI Constants: Visual theming, animations, hotkeys
Site Adapters: Domain-specific selectors for manga sites
Security: Encryption settings, license validation, data retention
Performance: Memory limits, timeouts, batch processing limits
Error Codes: Standardized error identifiers
Events: Custom DOM event names
Key Features:
Deep Freezing: All constants are immutable to prevent runtime modification
Multiple Export Formats: Supports CommonJS, AMD, ES Modules, and browser globals
Tree-Shaking Support: Individual exports for modern bundlers
Comprehensive Documentation: Inline comments explain each section
Environment Awareness: Different values for dev/staging/prod
Usage Examples:

// Import specific constants
import { STORAGE_KEYS, ERROR_CODES } from './constants.js';

// Use in code
chrome.storage.local.get(STORAGE_KEYS.SETTINGS);
throw new Error(ERROR_CODES.OCR_TIMEOUT);

// Or use the full object
import Constants from './constants.js';
console.log(Constants.EXTENSION.VERSION);

This centralizes all magic numbers, strings, and configuration values to make the codebase maintainable and prevent typos in repeated string literals.